    <note>Fang(1) Gan [17029] See Han Yuanji, WJ, 21.1a-1b for the ancestry of this lineage. Gan was a poet, who spent most of his life as a recluse in Shaoxing. The Tang zaixiang, Zhang(1) Wenwei (not in dataset), who served Zhaozong, memorialized for jinshi by grace for several people including Gan. He was privately given the posthumous name of Yuanying xiansheng. Renming Da cidian, p. 58. He was the Five Dynasty ancestor of the Taizhou, Linhai county Fang(1), and I am providing him with a son who moved there. See documentation for descendant, Congli (zi) [26104]. 《唐代人物知識ベース》記其生卒年為：809 - 888？.</note>
